@theonewolf 

"safe engineering practices dictate ranges of versions that are inclusive of their bounds, and have undergone full unit + integration testing with the software artifact." - correct !!! Key word - RANGES! If you can see in pull request developer did not use any range and he restricted lxml and requests libraries to only ONE version. It means users of package requests with version 2.18.3 can not use current app! Why ???

If you can read my suggestion was "add something like 'lxml>=4.0.0' (It means that your package works with lxml library with version 4 or greater)". Key word "something like" and example of range. Key word is RANGE. I gave example of lower range. Developers must know/test the lower safe range of related packages. And my proposal does not exclude upper range - for example 'lxml<5.0.0'. You are right... Possible it is also good idea to create restriction for next major release of lxml. Key word is MAJOR release, but not changes in docs.

