@mrpollo Perhaps, to keep this simple, we can go for something like the following:

```
class Vehicle():
    ...
    @property
    def is_armable(self):
        return GPS and EKF and MODE
    ...
```

And subclasses of Vehicle (using the vehicle_class mechansim) can just override is_armable(). Thus our code for simple_goto becomes:

```
print "Basic pre-arm checks"
while not vehicle.is_armable:
    time.sleep(1)
vehicle.armed = True
while not vehicle.armed:
   time.sleep(1)
```

This is still ugly, but we don't have any general solution yet for "await condition in user code with timeout" and that sounds like a larger, separate issue.

