@JacekHoleczek I think you are correct that there is a bit of a problem here. The local wrapper script indeed has a "/bin/env python" in the first line so if your default is now Python 2.7 then it will pick up that. However, if you want to make sure that your own script runs in Python 2.6, then you should in your own script insert a "/bin/env python2.6" magic line. If you depend on a specific python version, I would indeed always be specific.

